Theorem 2: (Zhou et al., 1999) If (A,C) is observable. Then:
trace(Q-1)=limɛ→0min {E([x(t)-x∧+(t)]*[x(t)-x∧+(t)])    + E([x(t)-x∧-(t)]*[x(t)-x∧-(t)]) }
where, Q is the generalized observability Gramian for the possibly unstable system (7). More details are discussed and proved in Zhou et al. (1999).
